'''Adam Holroyd''' (born 5 September 2004) is a professional [[rugby league]] footballer who plays as a {{rlp|sr}} forward for the [[Warrington Wolves]] in the [[Super League]].

In 2022 Holroyd made his début for [[Warrington Wolves|Warrington]] in the [[Super League]] against the [[Leeds Rhinos]].<ref name="bbc">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/62582817|title=Super League: Leeds Rhinos v Warrington Wolvest|work=BBC Sport |access-date=2022-10-01}}</ref>

On 7 June 2025, Holroyd played in Warrington's 8-6 Challenge Cup final loss against Hull Kingston Rovers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cn0gnqllpxlo|title=In pictures: Hull KR Challenge Cup victory parade|website=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>

